President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Tom Murphy as Under Secretary for Benefits at the Department of Veterans Affairs. Murphy is currently the Principal Deputy Under Secretary for Benefits at the VA. Obama also intends to appoint several individuals to key administration posts, including Jerry MacArthur Hultin and Lisa A. Hallett as members of the American Battle Monuments Commission, Rebecca Hankins and Naomi L. Nelson as members of the National Historical Publications and Records Commission, Lee A. Feinstein as a member of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council, and Priscilla Levine Kersten and Jonathan S. Lavine as members of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council.